DescDetail: <<
The Big Brother Data Base (aka BBDB, `The BBDB') allows one to
maintain a database of addresses, URL's, telephone numbers, faces, and
other personal information.  It has been integrated into several email
and news clients (e.g., gnus, vm), so that, for example, one can edit
and manipulate information within such clients; such news and mail
clients can also perform various operations (e.g., name rewriting)
based on data stored in the bbdb.
<<
DescUsage: <<
To initialize the bbdb to be used with the mail composition, mail and
news readers that you use (i.e., to establish keybindings for various
mail and news packages), add a call to the function `bbdb-initialize'
with various arguments; see the bbdb documentation for more
information.  For example, to initialize the bbdb for use with the
message composition package (which gnus uses) and gnus, add the form

  (bbdb-initialize 'message 'gnus)

to your emacs initialization file.  Again, see the info docs for more
information on how to call `bbdb-initialize' for your particular
needs.

XEmacs users: bbdb is already available within xemacs itself through
xemacs's own package management system.  See also the package
`xemacs-sumo-pkg', which contains the bbdb.
<<
